## Including RMD-graphics and R-plots in github pages (jekyll)

I wanted to be able to post a graph every now and then. [R Studio](http://www.rstudio.com) is able to render any graph you might create with R-code as data-URI-scheme via the r-markdown (rmd) module. Which is cool, because then you don't have to handle any files, just copy/paste the string of code.

In my first attempt, I wanted to show you guys the square root of all integers from 1 to 100. Here it comes:

<img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" />

The code used to generate this was `plot(sqrt(1:100))`. The process went like this:

1. create an .rmd file with the above shown r-code (or any other plot you wish to show the world) in it. You can find my spare file here https://github.com/rasmusvelling/r-plots-in-githubpages
2. 'Knit' the rmd file in RStudio and export to an html file.
3. Open the HTML in a proper browser like Chrome, view page source. The plot data string looks like: `data:image/png;base64,iV...`. You need to include the `<img>` tag for it to work as wells.
4. So find your plot in the source code: somethin like this:`<img src="data:image/png;base64,iVBO[... very long data string ...]>`. Copy that string.
5. Paste it in the .md file for your github page repo. 

And voila!
